# All text files in this repo are stored and checked out as LF, regardless
# of the user's core.autocrlf setting.  The Mako-driven codegen reads the
# template files verbatim and writes their bytes into generated C headers;
# if Windows checkout were to inject CRLF, MSVC's /utf-8 preprocessor would
# refuse to splice `\<CR><LF>` macro-continuation lines and the generated
# code would fail to compile.
*               text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-suspenders for the formats we ship.
*.c             text eol=lf
*.h             text eol=lf
*.py            text eol=lf
*.json          text eol=lf
*.md            text eol=lf
*.txt           text eol=lf
*.build         text eol=lf
meson.build     text eol=lf
meson_options.txt text eol=lf
.gitignore      text eol=lf
.gitattributes  text eol=lf
LICENSE         text eol=lf
